  "prompt": "What is the best quiz question asked ever?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" quiz question ever asked is subjective and can vary based on context, purpose, and audience. However, a question that is often celebrated for its historical and impactful nature in quizzes is:\n\n\"What is the only man-made object observable from space with the naked eye?\"\n\nThe common assumption is \"The Great Wall of China,\" but this is actually a myth. No man-made single structure is visible from space with the naked eye. This question is effective because it challenges common misconceptions and invites people to rethink widely accepted beliefs. For many, such questions that debunk myths can be the most intriguing in a quiz setting.",
